IMMEDIATE
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
CABINET SECRETARIAT
(Department of Cabinet Affairs)
New Delhi, the 27th June, 1970.
6th Asadha, 1892.
The undersigned is directed to state that with
effect from the afternoon of June 26, 1970,
(i) Shri K. Hanumanthaiya assumed the office of
Minister of Law and Social Welfare;
(ii) Shri K. Raghu Ramaiah relinquished the office of
Miništer (of state) of Parliamentary Affairs, and
Shipping & ransport, and assumed the office of
Minister of Parliamentary Affairs, and Shipping &
Transport;
(iii) Shri Nitiraj Singh Chaudhary assumed the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Petroleun and
Chemicals and Mines & Metals;
(iv) Shri parimal chosh assumed the office of Minister
of State in the Ministry of Health and Family
Planning and Works, Housing & Urban Development;
(v) Shri Narendra Singh Mahida assumed the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Defence;
(vi) Shri Ram Niwas Mirdha assum ed the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of Home Affairs.
(vii) Dr. (Smt) Nandini Satpathy relinquished the office
of Deputy Minister, and assumed the office of
Minister of State;
(viii) Shri K.R. Canesh assumed the office of Deputy
Minis ter in the Ministry of Finance; and
(ix) Shri Jagannath Pahadia assumed the office of
Deputy Minister in the Ministry of Food,
Agriculture, Community Development and Cooperation.
